# Plan: Researching Pexels and Pixabay API Keys

## Progress Tracking
- [x] Navigate to Pexels API and research free key process
- [x] Navigate to Pixabay API and research free key process
- [x] Summarize steps, costs, and hurdles
- [x] Final report to user

## Findings
### Pexels
- URL: https://www.pexels.com/api/
- Steps:
    1. Create a Pexels account or log in.
    2. Go to the API page and click "Get Started" or visit https://www.pexels.com/api/new/.
    3. Fill out the application form (Project Name, Category, Description) and agree to terms.
- Free status: Yes, free.
- Hurdles: Requires a brief description of how you will use the API; manual form entry.
- Rate Limit: 200 requests per hour (20,000 per month).

### Pixabay
- URL: https://pixabay.com/api/docs/
- Steps:
    1. Create a Pixabay account or log in.
    2. Visit the API documentation page (https://pixabay.com/api/docs/).
    3. Your API key will be automatically displayed in the "Parameters" -> "key" section.
- Free status: Yes, free.
- Hurdles: None; key is immediately available upon login.
- Rate Limit: 100 requests per minute (6,000 per hour).
